I"<p>Earlier this year, Senator Thom Tillis (who sits on the Senate Judiciary Committee, the committee that oversees copyright law) circulated a <a href="/docs/tillis-copyright-reform-questions.pdf">list of questions</a> asking for input about ways to modernize copyright law.  A number of organizations submitted extensive, substantive answers to these questions.  Piggybacking on that work, I submitted a <a href="/docs/tillis-copyright-reform-questions-response.pdf">brief letter</a> calling for two things.</p>
